{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d40cbe08-67fb-48d7-9c3d-67a50b4e7ecf","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP), VSTest flags are replaced by built-in MTP extensions. Here's the mapping:\n\n| VSTest flag | MTP equivalent | NuGet package needed |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect code-coverage` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` | *(same package)* |\n| `--filter` | `--filter` | *(unchanged)* |\n\n**New command:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect code-coverage \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nThe `--` separator passes everything after it to the MTP test host. Make sure you add the four extension packages to your test project(s).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d423dc82-c7dd-47ec-ad8f-17383e1d0a60","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect code-coverage` (with Microsoft.CodeCoverage package) or handled differently\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nI need to clarify how MTP works on .NET 8 specifically. With MTP, the command-line interface changes significantly from VSTest. On .NET 8, you can still use `dotnet test` with MTP integration, though the full MTP support in `dotnet test` is more mature starting in .NET 9. For .NET 8, you might run the test host directly or use `dotnet test` with the new platform-specific flags. For .NET 8 with MTP, the equivalent flags are `--filter` for filtering tests, `--report-trx` for TRX logging (requires the TrxReport package), `--collect code-coverage` for code coverage (needs CodeCoverage package), and `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` options for crash and hang diagnostics (each requiring their respective extension packages). When using `dotnet test` with the newer MTP integration, you can pass these flags together to get the same diagnostic capabilities as the older `dotnet test` command.","outputTokens":1123,"requestId":"A034:1FF93E:C2CC1D:E3D9B5:69FE86D3"},"id":"a9990cdb-5d95-4201-9e90-c6432e4ad714","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:59:18.141Z","parentId":"5ba2d2fc-f629-4b92-a3f3-b90ebc0bd3de"}
